 a\nnew set of hydrodynamical simulations. We apply this method to a sample of 158\nSPT-selected clusters, spanning the redshift range $0.05 < z < 1.35$, and\nmeasure $\\alpha = 0.017^{+0.030}_{-0.028}$, consistent with the standard model\nprediction of $\\alpha=0$. In combination with other published results, we\nconstrain $\\alpha = 0.011 \\pm 0.016$, an improvement of $\\sim 20\\%$ over\npublished constraints. This measurement also provides a strong constraint on\nthe effective equation of state in models of decaying dark energy\n$w_\\mathrm{eff} = -0.987^{+0.016}_{-0.017}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Dec 2013 15:20:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-18"}
